          "datePublished": "2025-10-02",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "1",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Title: Strongly Not Recommended — My Experience as a Concerned Parent\n\nI am very disappointed with this school. In my experience, there is clear discrimination in how students are treated — children who are related to or close with certain teachers are given priority over others. The school also charges excessively high fees for even the smallest events, as if they are organizing a flight, which feels unfair and exploitative.\n\nThe emphasis here is only on getting marks rather than on real learning. Teachers are frequently rotated — in my observation they change every three months — which disrupts continuity and hurts the students’ progress. Overall, the atmosphere feels biased and focused on appearances and numbers rather than genuine education.\n\nIf you value your time and money, I would advise you not to enroll your child in this school. Based on my experience, it is not worth the investment.\n",
          "publisher": {
            "@type": "Organization",
            "name": "Yellow Slate"
          }
